# FindMyPaper: ArXiv Paper Interactive Portal

FindMyPaper is an interactive web portal designed to help users explore and analyze over 1.7 million scholarly papers from the ArXiv metadata dataset. Through a suite of visualizations, users can navigate citation networks, author collaborations, and field-level trends across disciplines such as Computer Science, Physics, and Mathematics.

## Features

- **By-Category Statistics**: Pie charts, bar graphs, line graphs, and heatmaps showing publication trends over time.
- **Search & Save**: Filter papers by title, author, or keyword, and save favorites for later.
- **Authorâ€“Paper Graph**: A 3D bipartite network showing relationships between authors and their papers.
- **Co-Author Network**: Interactive 2D and 3D graphs highlighting academic collaboration structures.
- **Citation Graph**: Multi-level citation visualization from field to subfield to semantic clusters.
- **Graph Cities**: A geolocation-based visualization of global research hubs.

##  Installation

git clone https://github.com/yourusername/findmypaper.git
cd findmypaper
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
python app.py